	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Please people, look at the minimum specs a little more carefully. These are things I know from experience: When a game company gives minimum specs, they are OVER-estimating the minimum specs required. What Verant is telling you is that a PII-400 with a 16MB D3D-compatible video card is the absolute minimum that they garantee will run without lag or frame-rate slowdowns.<BR>
<BR>
And even though they list the GeForce 2 specifically under their &quot;recommended&quot;, ANY 32MB D3D-compatible video card will work (such as TnT2, Voodoo5, Viper 770, etc.) Also note that the GeForce 2 has been out almost a year, and costs around $100 retail for the 32MB card.<BR>
<BR>
Also keep in mind that the recommended (as opposed to the minimum) specs listed are for the &quot;power&quot; gamers who want to ramp up the clip plane and detail settings to their absolute max. <BR>
<BR>
This is not meant to put anyone down, just a reality check. You don't need a &quot;powergamer&quot; machine to enjoy the new graphics in the expansion, but neither should you be sitting there with a P200 and 8MB video card.<BR>
<BR>
(P.S.: There are also several Windows 95/98/ME tweaks that help improve graphics performance without overclocking, but they take too much explanation to display here.)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
